The Vice President, Mike Pence, visited the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) in Atlanta, Georgia to express gratitude for their efforts in combating the coronavirus pandemic. Pence thanked the CDC team for their dedication and hard work in saving lives across America. He also acknowledged the support and partnership of Senator David Perdue, Senator Kelly Loeffler, and Congressman Doug Collins in the national response to the pandemic. Pence emphasized the importance of following public health measures such as handwashing, social distancing, and wearing masks. He expressed hope for the upcoming approval and distribution of the first coronavirus vaccine, and praised the CDC's ongoing guidance and advice to the American people. Pence concluded by commending the CDC's compassionate and dedicated service, expressing confidence in overcoming the pandemic, and thanking Dr. Robert Redfield for his leadership.